1️⃣ Root Directory

The root directory / is the top of the Linux file system.

All files and folders start from /.

Example:

/
├── bin
├── etc
├── home
├── var
└── usr
2️⃣ Important Linux Directories
📁 /bin

Contains basic commands used by all users.
Example: ls, cp, mv, cat

📁 /etc

Stores configuration files for the system.

📁 /home

Contains user home directories.
Example:

/home/vishal
📁 /root

Home directory for the root (admin) user.

📁 /usr

Contains applications and program files.

📁 /var

Stores variable data like logs, cache, mail.

📁 /tmp

Temporary files stored here.

📁 /dev

Contains device files (hard disk, USB, etc.).

📁 /boot

Files needed for system booting.

3️⃣ Simple Structure
/
├── bin
├── boot
├── dev
├── etc
├── home
│   └── vishal
├── root
├── tmp
├── usr
└── var
4️⃣ Example Path
/home/vishal/file.txt

Meaning:

/ → root

home → user directory

vishal → user folder

file.txt → file

✅ Short Definition:
Linux File System is the structure used by Linux to organize files and directories starting from the root /.

